The paper discusses deep reinforcement learning and generative adversarial networks, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and robotics (cs.RO). The focus on preventing forgetting in sequential learning tasks also suggests a connection to continual learning, which is often studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence sub-categories.
